abstract: MSNBC is removing Lawrence O'Donnell from his 8 p.m. show and sending him back to 10 p.m., while "The Ed Show" will move from 10 to 8.
snippet: MSNBC is removing Lawrence O'Donnell from his 8 p.m. show and sending him back to 10 p.m., while "The Ed Show" will move from 10 to 8.
lead_paragraph: 5:19 p.m. | Updated MSNBC, which has fallen back to third in the nightly prime-time ratings for news channels, is shuffling its host lineup, removing Lawrence O'Donnell from the 8 p.m. show and sending him back to 10 p.m., while "The Ed Show" moves from 10 to 8.
